- The controller has a class-level @RequestMapping("/api/paste"), so every method's path is prefixed with /api/paste.
- The method getCodePasteFromId is annotated @GetMapping(path = "/{paste_id}") â†’ this yields /api/paste/{paste_id} for GET.
- There is also a separate method deleteCodePasteWithId annotated @DeleteMapping(path = "/{paste_id}"), so DELETE is also explicitly mapped to the same path.
- No other method-level mappings in the code bind to /{paste_id} (POST is mapped via @PostMapping but without the /{paste_id} path, so POST is for /api/paste, not /api/paste/{paste_id}).
- There are no explicit handlers for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, or PATCH in the source code for this path; therefore, based strictly on the code (per your instruction not to assume framework defaults), those methods are marked unacceptable.
- "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false because there is no @RequestMapping that explicitly allows all methods for this path.
